node.text:
If all of your debts are paid in full and the accounts are closed, you'll have what's called an "indeterminable" credit score after about 6 months. Then, you'll be able to do what's called "manual underwriting" to buy a home. All that means is that the mortgage company will do what banks used to do all the time when someone bought a home. They'll actually review your finances to check out whether or not you're in a position to pay back the loan.

A mortgage is the only type of debt, I'm okay with. Just make sure that the payment is no more than 25% of your take-home pay on no more than a 15-year mortgage at a fixed rate. I want your house to be a financial blessing in your life, not a financial curse.

You CAN have financial peace. You just need to take your time and do the math to make sure things are done right.

Thanks to Dr. @johndelony for joining me on this call. 

#debtfreecommunity 
#mortgage

node.text:
There's an addictive thrill that can come with the risk on these sorts of things. Although a lot of people are having a lot of fun with this right now, it's important to not confuse a get-rich-quick scenario with an actual, proven wealth-building plan. Just because a few people won the lottery one time does NOT make it an investment strategy that you should use. If you're debt-free with a full emergency fund, and you want to use some fun/entertainment money that you've budgeted for to play around with these things, I'm not gonna get mad at you, but I don't recommend it… and I certainly don't do this myself. If you REALLY want to play around with single stocks, just make sure that no more than 10% of your net worth is tied up in them. This is to ensure that things don't go overboard to the point that it can actually impact your net worth in a negative way if and when things go south. 

Reminder: I only recommend investing in mutual funds and real estate that's paid for in full.

node.text:
Great conversation with @kencoleman.

Budgeting isn't easy at first, but it's worth it. You've got to push through a few months to learn how to get your budget right. It's only when the pain of where you are exceeds the pain of making the change that you will actually decide to CHANGE. The struggle at the beginning is part of the learning process.

Push through— you'll get there. You can do this! 💪

#debtfreecommunity

node.text:
People who become wealthy and stay wealthy are the tortoise, never the hare. Every time I read the book, the tortoise wins. Slow down. You'll enjoy your life a little more too.

Great conversation with @johndelony. 

#debtfreecommunity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'DON'T CHASE HAPPINESS WITH MONEY. YOU'LL NEVER CATCH IT.'.

node.text: Yep, money can get you things and make life a little easier, but it won't bring you true happiness. That's something you can't buy. You've got to get it from a different source.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'DON'T PAY FOR INSURANCE COVERAGE THAT YOU DON'T NEED. R'.

node.text:
If you want to save money, checking up on your insurance rates and coverage can be a BIG help. Depending on your specific situation, some types of insurance could be a waste of money, so it's important to reevaluate things yearly.

An independent insurance professional can walk you through the coverage that's right for you and shop around to find you great rates.

Contact one that my team trusts and recommends in your area!

🔗Link in profile.

#debtfreecommunty

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Dave Ramsey @DaveRamsey You will win with money when you decide that your family's future is more important than any new toy you want to ouy'.

node.text:
If your actions don't align with your goals, what's the point of making them? Don't settle. Grow up and create the life you actually want! 

#debtfreecommunity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
WAY TO GO!!!!! 👏

#repost @jasminedenisse

I was one of the lucky ones to graduate my degree with ONLY $30k+ in debt.

But I also have to acknowledge the work I put in from school age to ensure I got the scholarships I needed going into college, knowing I was going to do it all on my own as a first gen - acknowledge the three jobs I worked through my last two years of college to avoid more debt - I missed out on so much. Having to saying no to things when I wanted to say yes. All that and so much more to say, I am proud of myself. I’m acknowledging my hard work and sacrifice and am so grateful for the support system I had and have. I don’t owe anyone anything and it feels SO good.

Shoutout to @daveramsey’s YouTube videos for keeping me fired up. I’m changing my family tree 💜

PS I don’t want this to be used as a “model minority” story that dismisses the idea that the student loan crisis doesn’t prey on those trying to achieve higher education - especially first generation minorities. So much had to go right for me to get here. No one should have to be so ridiculously in debt for an education. Forgiving student loans and changing the system as a whole to not be a vulture is what will create sustainable improvements on people’s lives!!!

#debtfreecommunity #debtfreescream

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Notes There are 2 types of people: 2. 1. Those who tell their money where to go. Those who wonder where it went.'.

node.text:
YOU are in control of your money. Not the other way around. Make a plan, and make it work! 💪

#debtfreecommunity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'DO NOT ACCEPT WHEN SOMEONE TELLS YOU, "IT CAN'T BE DONE."'.

node.text:
Your goals MATTER. Don't give up when it starts to get difficult. Don't give up if someone has something negative to say about your financial plans. The only person you need to impress is YOU.

#debtfreecommunity

We are asking everyone to pray for him at 8:30 this morning. If you can find a moment to go before the throne I would consider it a favor.'.

Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 29, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Dave Ramsey @DaveRamsey Maybe before we forgive student loan debt, we should stop allowing student loan debt...'.

node.text:
You've got to stop a problem at its source before you begin cleaning up the mess it's making. 

#debtfreecommunity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 29, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A0% LOAN IS STILL DEBT 只'.

node.text:
If you can't buy something with cash, don't buy it. Debt is debt. It will hurt you, no matter what the interest rate is. Your future matters TOO MUCH to give your money away to payments. You deserve better than that, and the first step to getting there is to STOP taking on more debt.

#debtfreecommunity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'DEBT FREE $57,153.46 IN 31 MONTHS PROVERBS 22'.

node.text:
So cool. SO proud of you two!! 

#repost @_kirsty_leigh_

WE’RE DEBT FREE!

That feels good to say, but it does not feel real yet. Today we sent the last penny to Toyota & I feel the weight off my shoulders. From the second jobs me & Ryan both picked up, at planet fitness & picking up trash at an apartment complex. We finally did it!

I will never forget the days where we waiting for Neilson Family Survey checks to come in the mail so we could get gas! I can not imagine going through FPU & this crazy journey with anyone else.

Thank you for all the support from our friends & family along the way & OF COURSE, thank you Dave 🤍 BABY STEP 3 HERE WE COME! #daveramsey #daveramseybabysteps #daveramseybudget #debtfreecommunity

node.text:
Short-term thinking or long-term thinking, it's up to you.

#debtfreecommunity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dave Ramsey on July 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE RICH TO INVEST.'.

node.text:
Investing isn't reserved for fancy, elite people who already have a lot of money to put into it. If you're debt-free (except for your home) with an emergency fund of 3-6 months of expenses saved, you're ready to start investing 15% of your income for retirement. If you're not there yet, keep working on those first 3 Baby Steps, and you'll be ready sooner than you think!

To begin investing, get in touch with a SmartVestor Pro that my team recommends to teach you about how to make and achieve your investing goals.

🔗 Link in profile.

#debtfreecommunity
